    <p>Both work. WordPress + WooCommerce offers more flexibility. Webflow built-in commerce is simpler. This use case demonstrates how the right tool can significantly improve productivity and outcomes. Users in this category should evaluate which platform better addresses their specific pain points and workflow requirements before making a decision.</p>
  </div>
  

    <h2>Final Verdict</h2>

    <div class="verdict">
      <p>WordPress offers more flexibility and a mature content management system.</p>
      <p>Webflow offers better design control and an all-in-one platform.</p>
      <p>Choose WordPress for content. Choose Webflow for design. Both WordPress and Webflow are excellent choices in the productivity category. Your final decision should be based on your specific requirements, budget, and preferred workflow. We recommend testing both platforms with their free tiers before committing to a paid plan.</p>
